01:33:20,430 --> 01:33:21,490
Thanks, Katie, for coming.

1436
01:33:22,470 --> 01:33:23,780
Thank you for asking me.

1437
01:33:24,430 --> 01:33:26,260
You stubborn old bastard.

1438
01:33:31,910 --> 01:33:34,420
I think I'll go
and freshen up, yeah?

1439
01:33:34,630 --> 01:33:35,660
All right.

1440
01:34:28,750 --> 01:34:31,580
Can somebody, er,
phone an ambulance, please? 9-9-9.

1441
01:34:31,590 --> 01:34:33,860
There's a guy collapsed in the toilet.
He's flat out.

1442
01:34:33,990 --> 01:34:36,660
Phone 9-9-9. Somebody, please.

1443
01:34:37,190 --> 01:34:38,330
Dan!

1444
01:34:38,510 --> 01:34:40,300
No! Dan!

1445
01:34:43,150 --> 01:34:44,580
Just had a heart attack.
Yeah, two breaths, please.

1446
01:34:44,590 --> 01:34:45,780
Oh, Dan!

1447
01:34:46,190 --> 01:34:49,380
- Just the two breaths...
- Is he breathing?

1448
01:34:49,710 --> 01:34:51,420
Oh, Dan.

1449
01:34:51,550 --> 01:34:52,840
Listen, we're trying to help
him as much as we can.

1450
01:34:52,870 --> 01:34:55,580
No, no, no, please keep going,
please keep going. Don't stop.

1451
01:34:55,590 --> 01:34:56,910
I'm afraid we've lost him.

1452
01:34:57,110 --> 01:35:01,580
No, don't say that,
please don't say that. No.

1453
01:35:02,590 --> 01:35:05,180
- No, please!
- I'm so sorry.

1454
01:35:05,310 --> 01:35:06,340
I'm sorry.

1455
01:35:06,590 --> 01:35:09,100
- Please...
- Where's the ambulance now?

1456
01:35:09,430 --> 01:35:11,700
- Please.
- No response at all.

1457
01:35:17,310 --> 01:35:19,690
Please. Please try again.

1458
01:36:11,790 --> 01:36:12,820
Erm...

1459
01:36:13,750 --> 01:36:18,820
They call this a "pauper's funeral"
because it's the cheapest slot, at 9:00.

1460
01:36:21,310 --> 01:36:22,860
But Dan wasn't a pauper to us.

1461
01:36:24,670 --> 01:36:27,420
He gave us things that money can't buy.

1462
01:36:30,910 --> 01:36:32,700
When he died, I found this on him.

1463
01:36:35,550 --> 01:36:37,460
He always used to write in pencil.

1464
01:36:39,470 --> 01:36:40,500
Erm...

1465
01:36:41,310 --> 01:36:45,700
And he wanted to read it at his appeal
but he never got the chance to.

1466
01:36:48,670 --> 01:36:51,540
And I swear that this lovely man,

1467
01:36:52,630 --> 01:36:53,980
had so much more to give,

1468
01:36:56,070 --> 01:36:59,260
and that the State drove him
to an early grave.

1469
01:37:03,430 --> 01:37:04,700
And this is what he wrote.

1470
01:37:07,230 --> 01:37:12,300
"I am not a client, a customer,
nor a service user.

1471
01:37:13,870 --> 01:37:18,730
"I am not a shirker, a scrounger,
a beggar, nor a thief.

1472
01:37:19,830 --> 01:37:23,740
"I'm not a National Insurance Number
or blip on a screen.

1473
01:37:25,030 --> 01:37:29,140
"I paid my dues, never a penny short,
and proud to do so.

1474
01:37:30,750 --> 01:37:35,690
"I don't tug the forelock, but look my
neighbour in the eye and help him if I can.

1475
01:37:36,950 --> 01:37:39,380
"I don't accept or seek charity.

1476
01:37:41,310 --> 01:37:46,380
"My name is Daniel Blake.
I am a man, not a dog.

1477
01:37:47,510 --> 01:37:49,780
"As such, I demand my rights.

1478
01:37:51,150 --> 01:37:53,380
"I demand you treat me with respect.

1479
01:37:55,110 --> 01:37:58,500
"I, Daniel Blake, am a citizen,

1480
01:37:59,790 --> 01:38:02,350
"nothing more and nothing less."

1481
01:38:03,630 --> 01:38:04,690
Thank you.

